          <td width="30">&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="405" class="texte">
FULL TIME POSITION, Bordeaux France<BR><BR>We are one of the world-leaders in our business. You will participate in a dynamic multimedia communication policy aimed at helping us  reinforce and build on that positioning  You will be reporting to the Head of Brand and Communications.<BR><BR>Principle duties and responsibilities<BR> <BR>·	You will ensure the deployment of our gaming and corporate on-line supports (web sites and newsletters) <BR><BR>·	You will develop, in the countries in which we are active, the communication road map for our portfolio of games (using specialized media, partners and clients)<BR><BR>·	You will responsible for all of the IN FUSIO external contacts data base <BR><BR>·	You will develop and ensure the correct application of our graphic charter <BR><BR><BR>Education, experience and skills required<BR><BR>·	You have a Degree (Masters or Bachelors) in Marketing, Business or Public Relations<BR>·	You have at least 5 years experience in public relations or web marketing, 3 of which are in a management role <BR><BR>·	Ideally, this experience has been acquired in an international context <BR><BR>·	Understanding our sector (video games / mobile phone industry) would be a definite advantage<BR><BR><BR>·	Extremely involved in your job, a proactive individual, you regularly propose new solutions <BR><BR>·	Rigorous and methodical, you are highly reliable in your work <BR><BR>·	You have excellent people skills, and you know what “team work” means <BR><BR>·	You have good writing skills <BR><BR>·	You are fluent in English and French. Another language (German, Italian or Spanish) would be appreciated <BR><BR><BR><BR>
<B></B><BR>
If you are flexible, dynamic and you are eager to be part of the growth of this highly international company (English is the working language), then please send us your CV.<BR><BR>We feel it is very important to help develop the skills of all our employees.<BR>Thus, in order to help you along your career path, we do our<BR>best to maximize the possibility of internal promotion.<BR><BR><BR><BR>
<B></B><BR>
<BR><BR>
